# Toronto Rising — multiplayer authority (pre–second-client)

> **⚠ PREMISE UNDER ACTIVE CORRECTION (2026-07-04) — READ FIRST.** The premise that "TTS runs `onLoad` / event handlers on **every client**" (which the host-**execution** rules below depend on) is contradicted by the authoritative TTS model: **mod Lua runs on the host only; connected clients do not run the Global script or object scripts.** See [`Execution Model Correction — Remediation Plan`](../../.dev/Multiplayer%20Functionality/Execution%20Model%20Correction%20%E2%80%94%20Remediation%20Plan.md). **Until that plan completes, for any new or modified code:**
> - **Do NOT add** new `U.isHostClient()`, `U.requireHostForWorldMutation()`, `GlobalRequireHostForWorldMutation`, or `requireStorytellerHostForMutation` **execution** guards. The P1–P2 / P5–P8 host-*execution* mandates below are **suspended for new code**.
> - **Do NOT ad-hoc remove** existing guards either — removal is **staged** in the remediation plan (Step 3), not free-for-all.
> - **STILL CORRECT (keep applying):** actor-identity gating via `U.isStorytellerSteamPlayer(playerRef)` ("*who* triggered this ST-only action") and per-client XmlUI `visibility` targeting (`Black`/`Admin`/`<Color>`). These are unaffected by the correction.

**Until TOR-144 (multiplayer E2E) passes with two real clients**, treat solo Host Save & Play as **insufficient** proof for fan-out / join-client behavior. **`U.isHostClient()` is always true when developing alone** — do not treat that as multiplayer validation.

Canonical policies **P1–P10**, pre-flight checklist, and first-session script: [`.dev/Multiplayer Functionality/Preparing For Multiplayer.md`](../../.dev/Multiplayer%20Functionality/Preparing%20For%20Multiplayer.md) §1.

Audit playbook for agents: [`.dev/Multiplayer Functionality/Multiplayer Performance Audit.md`](../../.dev/Multiplayer%20Functionality/Multiplayer%20Performance%20Audit.md).

## Mandatory on every feature touching players, objects, load, or world I/O

1. **Classify delivery:** fan-out (`onLoad`, `onObjectDrop`, `Global.call`, …) vs clicker-only (`HUD_*`, object `click_*`).
2. **Classify tier:** A UI / B state / C world — [Bootstrap Authority](../../.dev/Sychronizing%20Game%20Functionality/Bootstrap%20Authority.md).
3. **Tier C → Host only:** `U.requireHostForWorldMutation(context)` before spawns, moves, lights, audio, `Sync.npcs`, reconciler world apply. **Chunk load and `onLoad` included** (not only `onObjectDrop`).
4. **ST interaction vs Host machine:** `U.isStorytellerSteamPlayer(playerRef)` for who acted; **never** steam-only on fan-out (every client sees ST steam when ST drops a token).
5. **Join-client Tier C from PC UI/objects:** route through **`Global.call`** to a Global entry that host-guards internally (`GlobalIsStorytellerSteamPlayer`, `GlobalRequireHostForWorldMutation` for object scripts).
6. **Do not** host-guard an entire fan-out handler when only Tier C is host-only (rolls: Tier B FSM may run on all clients; lights via `Sync.player` on host only).
7. **Object scripts:** no `require("core.*")` for mutations — pattern: `objects/npc_control_board.ttslua`, `objects/dice_bag.ttslua`.
8. **New handlers:** add a row to [Event Listener Policy](../../.dev/Sychronizing%20Game%20Functionality/Event%20Listener%20Policy.md) (delivery + tier).
9. **Do not** remove host guards to fix join-client HUD staleness — live `gameState` broadcast is a known gap (P10); world authority stays on Host.

## Agent completion checklist (Lua / sync changes)

Before marking work done:

- [ ] Tier C paths host-guarded; ST XmlUI uses `requireStorytellerHostForMutation` or equivalent (steam + host).
- [ ] Fan-out hot paths: O(1) tag/GUID guard before `require` / `Sync.*` (TOR-197).
- [ ] Mutation → narrow `Sync.*`; no dual apply without fingerprint ([Dual-apply survey](../../.dev/Sychronizing%20Game%20Functionality/Dual_apply_survey.md)).
- [ ] Event Listener Policy inventory updated if handlers added/changed.
- [ ] Solo smoke if touching gameboard or rolls (Apply/Clear, one roll path); note **multiclient unverified** in Linear comment unless TOR-144 exercised.

## High-risk surfaces (grep when touching)

Load/bootstrap, gameboard Apply/Clear, token drop/pick-up, scenes/soundscape HUD, dice/rolls, signal candle, character sheet mutators, player connect/seat — see Preparing §1.3.

## Linear

Host-authority mechanical work is **not Done** until **TOR-144 (multiplayer E2E)** passes. Comment on related issues when adding fan-out or Global mutators.
